{"cursor":"8226","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"A 'public service' is a service which is provided by government to people living\nwithin its jurisdiction, either directly (through the public sector) or by\nfinancing private provision of services. The term is associated with a social\nconsensus (usually expressed through democratic elections) that certain services\nshould be available to all, regardless of income. Even where public services are\nneither publicly provided nor publicly financed, for social and political\nreasons they are usually subject to regulation going beyond that applying to\nmost economic sectors. Public service is also a course that can be studied at a\ncollege and/or university.\n","linknr":334,"url":"Public_services","recorded":1362560717,"links":34,"instances":["economics","economics","economics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Political economy","Public administration","Public services|"],"headings":["Sectors","Characteristics","History","Nationalization","Privatization","Public services versus Services of General Interest","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5c/A_group_of_Damas_de_Rojo.jpg/220px-A_group_of_Damas_de_Rojo.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["service","economics"],["service","economics"],["good","accounting"],["good","economics"],["rivalry","economics"],["service","economics"]],"members":["good","rivalry","service"],"related":["Service_(economics)","Government","Public_sector","Democratic","Income","Regulation","Economic_sectors","Moral","Human_rights","Developed_countries","Electricity","Education","Environmental_protection","Fire_service","Gas","Health_care","Law_enforcement"